---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Workflow Automation | Intelio - Eliminate Coordination Bottlenecks" description="Eliminate coordination bottlenecks with automated workflows. Requests route themselves. Work moves continuously. No manual handoffs.">
<main class="bg-white">
  <!-- HERO SECTION: Video Background -->
  <section class="relative h-[600px] md:h-[450px] sm:h-[300px] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden bg-black">
    <!-- Video Background -->
    <video 
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
      playsinline
      preload="auto"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    >
      <source src="/videos/system-integration-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4">
      Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>
    
    <!-- Dark Overlay for Text Readability -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/45 z-[1]"></div>

    <!-- Hero Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-[48px] md:text-[36px] sm:text-[24px] text-white mb-4 leading-[1.2] font-normal tracking-[-0.5px]">
        Requests Route Themselves Automatically
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-base sm:text-sm text-[#f0f0f0] leading-relaxed font-normal max-w-[600px] mx-auto">
        No manual routing. No queue delays. No bottleneck person. Work flows continuously with the right person handling each request.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-6 sm:px-6">
    <!-- THE PROBLEM SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-24 md:pt-16 sm:pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        What's Broken Today
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-black leading-relaxed mb-12 font-normal">
        Most businesses have one person whose job is coordination: routing requests, assigning work, managing queues. When they're unavailable, everything stops.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Manual Routing Bottleneck
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Requests arrive and someone manually routes them to the right person, team, or department. This person is a bottleneck. Everything queues when they're unavailable.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Work Sitting in Queues
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Approval requests, lead assignments, support tickets—all waiting for someone to pick them up. Delays compound. Urgency gets lost in the queue.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Inconsistent Execution
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Same request gets handled differently depending on who picks it up. Lead A qualified in 2 hours, lead B in a week. Approval times are unpredictable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Lost Context at Handoffs
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Work passes from person A to person B and critical context is lost. "Why is this flagged urgent?" Information is fragmented across emails and systems.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT CHANGES SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        What Changes After Deployment
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-black leading-relaxed mb-12 font-normal">
        The system removes the coordination bottleneck by automatically routing, assigning, and tracking work.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Automatic Routing & Assignment
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Requests route themselves based on rules (skill, capacity, geography, complexity). No manual bottleneck. No queue delays waiting for someone to route.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Work Flows Continuously
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Requests are assigned and work begins within minutes, not days. Nothing sits waiting for someone to pick it up manually.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Consistent Execution
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Same workflow, same rules, every time. Approval times are predictable. Lead qualification is consistent. Response times are uniform across the team.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Context Travels with Work
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            When work is assigned, all relevant information moves with it. Customer history, previous interactions, decision context. No scrambling to find context.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8 md:col-span-2">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Automatic Status Updates
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Status changes trigger notifications automatically. Requestors, managers, and stakeholders stay informed without asking. Information flows instead of being manually copied.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW IT WORKS SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        How the System Actually Works
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-black mb-12 leading-relaxed font-normal">
        Requests are captured, classified, routed to the right person, and tracked automatically. Humans stay in control of decisions.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Input Layer
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Work enters from multiple sources: form submissions, system events (deal closed, invoice received), email, API calls, scheduled triggers. The system captures who submitted it, what it's about, when it arrived, any attachments, and where it came from.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Classification & Enrichment
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            The system classifies what type of work this is (support ticket, approval, lead, claim). It enriches the request with context: customer history, related records, previous similar requests, templates, and relevant business rules. This happens in seconds automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Routing Decision
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Rules determine who should handle this. Which team has expertise? Who has capacity? Is there geographic routing? Are there escalation rules (high-value to senior person, urgent to specialist)? The system applies your rules automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Assignment & Execution
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Work is assigned to the right person with full context, suggested action, SLA deadline, and links to related records. Status notifications go out automatically. If workflows can auto-execute (templated responses, task creation), they do. If they need approval, the approval request goes to the right person.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Oversight Layer
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed font-normal">
            Low-confidence routing gets human review. Unusual requests get escalated. Exceptions queue for manual handling. Nothing auto-executes when it shouldn't. Dashboards show workflow health so you see what's pending, what's backlogged, what failed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROOF OF PRODUCTION REALITY -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        This Actually Works
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-black mb-12 leading-relaxed font-normal">
        These workflows are handling mission-critical processes at scale right now.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            200-500
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-4 font-normal">
            Workflow executions per day
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-normal">
            5-15 distinct workflows per client. Running continuously for 90+ days with zero unplanned downtime.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            97%+
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-4 font-normal">
            On-time completion rate
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-normal">
            Up from 60-70% before automation. Consistency comes from rules, not people.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            5-7 hours/week
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-4 font-normal">
            Time freed from lead routing
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-normal">
            15-20 min per lead × 20 leads per week. Now available for revenue work, not coordination.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            2-3 days → 2-3 hours
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-4 font-normal">
            Approval queue time reduction
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-normal">
            Because approvals don't wait for someone to manually route them. They're assigned automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="p-8 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
          Mission-Critical Operations
        </h3>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed mb-4 font-normal">
          These workflows aren't optional improvements. They're critical paths in the business.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-base text-black list-none">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
            <span class="font-normal">Lead routing: Used for 100% of inbound leads. Stops and sales stops.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
            <span class="font-normal">Approval workflows: Used for all spending decisions. Turns off and nothing gets approved.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
            <span class="font-normal">Support routing: Used for 100% of incoming requests. Critical to SLA compliance.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
            <span class="font-normal">Onboarding: Eliminates the coordination bottleneck for new employee setup.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ENGAGEMENT MODELS SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        How We Work
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-black mb-12 leading-relaxed font-normal">
        Two engagement models. Clear ownership. Explicit responsibilities.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Build + Maintain
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 mb-6 italic font-normal">
            You own the workflows. We keep the system running.
          </p>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-black mb-1 font-normal">You own</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Day-to-day workflow monitoring, routing rules, exception handling, SLA accountability</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-black mb-1 font-normal">We own</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">System uptime, infrastructure health, technical updates, performance optimization</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed mb-4 p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg font-normal">
            Best for: Teams with an ops or process owner who wants hands-on control. You review exceptions, manage rule changes.
          </p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-normal">Project fee + monthly maintenance</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Build + Operate
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 mb-6 italic font-normal">
            We own the workflow execution and performance.
          </p>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-black mb-1 font-normal">You own</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Overall business outcomes and strategic priorities</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-black mb-1 font-normal">We own</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Daily execution, exception handling, rule changes, performance optimization, SLA compliance</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-base text-black leading-relaxed mb-4 p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg font-normal">
            Best for: Lean teams who want workflows to "just work" without daily management. You get accountability for execution quality.
          </p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-normal">Monthly operating retainer</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 p-8 border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-6 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
          What's Always Clear
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal">Work Ownership</p>
            <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Your team stays responsible for actual decisions (approvals, assignments). We manage the automation.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal">Rule Authority</p>
            <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">You control the logic. Changes go through you. You decide routing, SLA, escalation rules.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal">Escalation Path</p>
            <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">If something breaks, here's who gets notified first, who's accountable, and what the rollback procedure is.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal">Cost Model</p>
            <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Based on workflow complexity and execution volume. Transparent. No surprises.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- COMMON PATTERNS SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-12 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Common Workflow Automations
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Lead Routing Workflow
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-normal">THE PROBLEM</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">New lead arrives. Someone manually routes it to a salesperson. Takes 15-20 minutes. Lead sits in a queue waiting for routing.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-normal">THE AUTOMATION</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Lead submitted → system enriches with company data, ICP score, LinkedIn info → routes based on territory, expertise, capacity → assigned to right rep with templates and customer history within 60 seconds.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-black mb-1 font-normal">RESULT</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Lead routed in 60 seconds vs. 20 minutes. Consistent routing. No high-quality leads missed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Approval Workflow
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-normal">THE PROBLEM</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Approval request submitted. Someone manually routes to the right approver. Request sits in queue. Approver gets it days later.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-normal">THE AUTOMATION</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Request submitted → system classifies (what's being approved?) → routes based on amount (under $5K to manager, $5K-$50K to head, over $50K to CFO) → approver gets request with context, previous similar approvals, policy rules → decision (approve/reject) → next process executes automatically.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-black mb-1 font-normal">RESULT</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Approval time 2-3 days → 2-3 hours. Nothing gets stuck. Budget tracked automatically.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Support Ticket Routing
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-normal">THE PROBLEM</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Support ticket arrives. Someone routes to an agent. Takes 30+ minutes. Customer sits with no response.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-normal">THE AUTOMATION</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Ticket submitted → classified by issue type (technical, billing, account) → prioritized (urgent? VIP? SLA critical?) → routed based on expertise and capacity → agent gets ticket with customer history, previous tickets, knowledge base suggestions, SLA deadline → customer notified automatically.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-black mb-1 font-normal">RESULT</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Right person gets ticket immediately. First-contact resolution improves. SLA met consistently.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Document Review Workflow
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-normal">THE PROBLEM</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Document needs approval. Someone routes to legal, finance, or executive. Documents get lost. Review takes days or weeks.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 font-normal">THE AUTOMATION</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Document submitted → classified (contract, proposal, case summary?) → routed through approval chain (legal? finance? executive?) → each reviewer gets document with context, related records, templates → decision (approve, approve with changes, reject) → approved docs filed automatically or sent to execution stage.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-black mb-1 font-normal">RESULT</p>
              <p class="text-base text-black font-normal">Documents approved in hours instead of days. Nothing gets lost. Audit trail complete.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RISK & CONTROL SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12 border-b border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-12 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Risk, Control & Ownership
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Workflow Logic
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-base text-black list-none">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">You own the rules that drive routing decisions</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">Documented, versioned, portable</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">If you leave us, you take your workflows</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">No proprietary lock-in</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Failure Handling
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-base text-black list-none">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">Real-time monitoring of all workflows</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">Immediate notification if workflow fails or queue backs up</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">Automatic retry for recoverable errors</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">Can pause all workflows immediately</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Human Oversight
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-base text-black list-none">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">System routes and processes; humans make decisions</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">Low-confidence routing goes to human review</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
              <span class="font-normal">Unusual requests escalate for approval</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-black mr-3 font-normal">•</span>
